  "rulesSkFlowTitle": "Turn Sequence",
  "rulesSkFlowBody": "1. In Round N, each player receives N cards. (Rounds 1–10)\n2. All players simultaneously predict (bid) the number of tricks they will win.\n3. Starting from the lead player, cards are played following suit-following rules.\n4. After each round, scores are calculated based on bid success/failure.",

  "rulesSkScoringTitle": "Scoring",
  "rulesSkScoringBody": "• Bid 0 success (0 tricks won): +10 × round number\n• Bid 0 failure: -10 × round number\n• Bid N success (exactly N tricks won): +20 × N + bonus\n• Bid N failure: -10 × |difference| (no bonus)\n• Bonuses are only awarded when the bid is exact.",

